						<section>
							<h2 class="h2_sub_title_v1">Employment</h2>

							<div class="summary_list_wrap mg_t5">
								<p class="text_type_v1">Employment opportunities for foreign residents vary according to type of visa. Marriage immigrants who have entered Korea under an F-13 or F-21 visa are allowed to seek employment in Korea.</p>

								<!-- 일자리 알선 기간 방문 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Job Centers</h3>
									<p class="text_type_v4">
										You can obtain information on employment for foreigners (marriage immigrants, etc.) by visiting your local Employment Center, Women Resources Development Center, Foreign Workforce Support Center, or Support Center for Mulitcultural Families.
									</p>
									<ol>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">1.Employment Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">These centers (83 branches nationwide as of August 2013) are representative job placement institutes run free of charge by the State. Korean and foreign jobseekers can inquire at job centers to learn about job openings at companies of interest or to receive career counseling. Company interviews are also held through the center until the jobseeker finds a job.</p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">2.Job Information Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">These local agencies provide free information on job opportunities. Job information centers are located at most city halls and county offices. The centers will help you find a job Exit to your residence.</p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">3.Women Resources Development Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">These comprehensive job placement support institutes for women focus mainly on job placement and training. Most of the programs are provided free of charge, but some may require a small fee.</p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">4.Foreign Workforce Support Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">These non-governmental organizations assist foreign workers in dealing with employment issues in Korea.</p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">5.Multicultural Family Support Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">These centers offer job opportunities and cultural programs for multicultural families.</p>
										</li>
									</ol>
								</section>
								<!-- //일자리 알선 기간 방문 -->

								<!-- 인터넷이용 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Use of the Internet</h3>
									<p class="text_type_v4">
										Marriage immigrants can use the Internet to aid in their search for employment. Most organizations operating employment services for marriage immigrants manage websites, so users can search for jobs from home via the Internet.
									</p>
									<ol>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">1.Seoul Global Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">This website is operated by the City of Seoul and provides information related to fairs and job seeking, and employment support to foreigners in Korea, in English and Chinese.
											</p>
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3"><a href="http://global.seoul.go.kr/index.do" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">Seoul Global Center Go to the website</a></p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">2.WorkNet
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">This employment portal site is run by the Ministry of Employment and Labor via the Korea Employment Information Service. Occupation and career information, and employment policy information are provided as well as information on job openings; jobseekers can submit job applications directly through the site.</p>
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3"><a href="http://www.work.go.kr/index.jsp" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">WorkNet Go to the website</a></p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">3.Employment & Welfare Center of the Ministry of Employment and Labor
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">This is a free job placement institution with a nationwide network. Through the site, jobseekers can get career counseling and are helped until they find a job. You can directly access the homepage of the Exitst employment & welfare center to your residence via the center's main website. The employment center runs various career guidance programs such as a shortterm group counseling program, and special lectures on employment, including the 'Career guidance program for married immigrant women (WIND)' for enhancing marriage immigrants’ ability to attain suitable employment. To help marriage immigrants having difficulty visiting companies for interviews, the center even provides counselors that will accompany marriage immigrants to their company of interest.</p>
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3"><a href="http://www.work.go.kr/jobcenter" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">Employment & Welfare Center of the Ministry of Employment and Labor Go to the website</a></p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">4.Women’s Resource Development Center
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">This center provides various job training programs, vocational training, and counseling for working women, and serves as a comprehensive job placement support institution for women.</p>
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3"><a href="http://www.vocation.or.kr" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">Women’s Resource Development Center Go to the website</a></p>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">5.Job Information Centers of Cities and Guns Local governments
											<p class="text_type_v2 mg_t3">This center operates free job brokerage organizations. Please refer to the websites of local governments for more information.</p>
										</li>
									</ol>
								</section>
								<!-- //인터넷이용 -->
