							<h2 class="h2_sub_title_v1">Vocational Training</h2>

							<div class="summary_list_wrap mg_t5">
								<p class="text_type_v1">Vocational training is a system that helps people who hope to open a business or work at a company to acquire technologies and skills. Foreigners can apply if they have a history of insured qualification, but married immigrants can receive support without this history.</p>

								<ul class="mg_t5">
									<li class="text_type_v5">Employment Center <a href="http://www.work.go.kr/jobcenter" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">(Employment Center Go to the website)</a></li>
									<li class="text_type_v5 mg_t5">Comprehensive counseling center, the Ministry of Employment and Labor(☎1350 or ☎1544-1350) <a href="tel:1350" class="color_pink text_underline">Make a Call</a></li>
									<li class="text_type_v5 mg_t5">Career capability development information network of the Ministry of Employment and Labor <a href="http://www.hrd.go.kr" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">(Career capability development information network of the Ministry of Employment and Labor Go to the website)</a></li>
								</ul>

								<!-- 내일배움카드제란 ? -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Nae-il-bae-um Card System ?</h3>
									<p class="text_type_v4">
										The system helps students to receive proper training by issuing them with a career capability development account (Nae-il-bae-um Card) to support training for the unemployed who need it.
									</p>
								</section>
								<!-- //내일배움카드제란 ? -->

								<!-- 지원대상 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Eligibility for support</h3>
									<p class="text_type_v4">
										The unemployed, small business owners over the age of 15 (provided the business period has been more than one year, and the annual sales amount is less than KRW 80 million)
									</p>
								</section>
								<!-- //지원대상 -->

								<!-- 지원내용 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Description</h3>
									<ol>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">1.Maximum support: Supports 50%~80% of the actual training costs up to a maximum of KRW 2 million per person (Trainee pays the remainder directly.)
											<ul>
												<li class="text_type_v10 mg_t5">Participants of type 2 in the employment success package receive 70%~90% of the actual training costs. Type 1 participants receive the whole amount of training, up to a maximum of KRW 3 million.</li>
												<li class="text_type_v10 mg_t5">The entire training costs are refunded to those who paid by themselves (the early employed, and graduates) and maintain their career for more than six month by working or starting business in the same job position within 6 months of the date of training completion.</li>
												<li class="text_type_v10 mg_t5">When a student attends 80% of the training days (per month), up to an additional KRW 116,000 is paid monthly.</li>
											</ul>
										</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">2.Expiration date: 1 year from account issuance date
											<ul>
												<li class="text_type_v10 mg_t5">If the applicant does not participate in training within 6 months from opening the account, the account is suspended and the remaining amount is abolished. If the account is re-opened, the previous support limit is reduced by 50%.</li>
											</ul>
										</li>
									</ol>
								</section>
								<!-- //지원내용 -->

								<!-- 지원대상 훈련과정 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Supported training courses</h3>
									<ol>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">1. Account-qualified training courses recognized and announced by the Ministry of Employment and Labor
											<ul>
												<li class="text_type_v10 mg_t5">Courses are recognized and announced as account-qualified training courses by the Minister of Employment and Labor through review during training course applied by the training institution. Search on the website of HRD-Net (<a href="http://www.hrd.go.kr" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">http://www.hrd.go.kr</a>) to attend training courses selected and negotiated by trainees and counselors of the employment center.
											</ul>
										</li>
									</ol>
								</section>
								<!-- //지원대상 훈련과정 -->

								<!-- 지원절차 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Application procedure</h3>

									<div class="procedure_wrap_v2">
										<ul>
											<li>
												<p class="tit">1. Training Counseling</p>
												<p class="txt">Job application and application for account / In-depth counseling (Center ↔ the unemployed)</p>
											</li>
											<li class="procedure_arrow"></li>
											<li>
												<p class="tit">2. Opening the account</p>
												<p class="txt">Review on necessity of training, and importance / Select opening of the account and training position (Center → the unemployed)</p>
											</li>
											<li class="procedure_arrow"></li>
											<li>
												<p class="tit">3. Attend courses</p>
												<p class="txt">Register training courses / Attend training courses (The unemployed ↔ training agency)</p>
											</li>
											<li class="procedure_arrow"></li>
											<li>
												<p class="tit">4. Support costs</p>
												<p class="txt">Apply for training fee per month / Training fee and training support subsidy are calculated and paid after checking attendance days (Hiring center)</p>
											</li>
										</ul>
									</div>

								</section>
								<!-- //지원절차 -->

								<!-- 기타 직업훈련 -->
								<section>
									<h3 class="h3_sub_title_v1 mg_t15">Other Job Training Services</h3>
									<ol>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">1. For married immigrant women, in addition to Nae-il-bae-um card system training conducted through employment insurance, other free or paid vocational training programs are available at Women Resources Development Center (<a href="http://www.vocation.or.kr" target="blank" class="color_pink text_underline">www.vocation.or.kr</a>), Women’s Community Center, etc.</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">2. Not all agencies offer job training services for married immigrant women and female foreigners; consult your nearest center before visiting.</li>
										<li class="text_type_v4 mg_t10">3. Further details are available at multicultural family support centers and related organizations.</li>
									</ol>
								</section>
